column3: Is someone testing all these mac changes on an actual mac?\n

Automatic sanity-testing: FAILED BUILD/TEST, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/a9957ce3d012fa3d9a0c8a3a9213b3ca9e0b6304 for binaries and test log.

This could happen for one of several reasons:
1. It chanages paths in makefile.linux-mingw or otherwise changes build scripts in a way that made them incompatible with the automated testing scripts
2. It does not build on either Linux i386

Failed because of `Error: An error occurred while setting up the RPC port 8332 for listening on IPv4: Address already in use`, which is unrelated to this patch. Seems to be a problem with BitcoinPullTester.\n
